gbw: Boundary layer conductance to water vapor per leaf area
CO2r: CO2 concentration in wet air entering chamber
CO2s: CO2 concentration in wet air inside chamber
gsw: Stomatal conductance to water vapor per leaf area
flow: Flow rate of air into chamber
plantHeight: The height of the plant measured
siteIdentifier: Location descriptor of where data was collected
A: Net CO2 exchange per leaf area
RHr: Relative humidity of air entering the chamber
RHs: Relative humidity of air inside the chamber
Tblock: Temperature of cooler block used to stabilize air temperature
E: Transpiration rate of H2O per leaf area
VPDleaf: Leaf to air vapor pressure deficit
dataContributor: Name of the individual or organization that contributed to the data
measurementDevice: Name of the instrument that collected data
instrumentType: Instrument make & model. Describe any custom modifications in comments
experimentalTreatment: Description of any applied sample manipulations
growthEnvironment: Description of the plant growth environment
unadjudicatedName: Full species name and subspecies if applicable
plantType: Classification of plant as either gymnosperm or angiosperm, indicating differences in reproductive structures and evolutionary lineage
plantLeaf: Leaf lifespan strategy of the plant, categorizing it as evergreen or deciduous based on leaf retention patterns
plantForm: Life form of the plant, categorizing it as tree, shrub, grass, crop, savanna, etc., based on growth form and ecological function
acceptedName: The accepted species name assigned by the adjudicator
nameAuthor: The author of the accepted species name
nameAuthority: The authority that was referenced to assign the accepted species name
nameCategory: The taxonomic heirarchy level at which the plant was named (family, genus, species, subspecies, variety, type)
nameAdjudicator: The expert that assigned an unadjudicated species name to an accepted species name
